        <p>Following are some examples of how you might create segmentation rules:</p>
        <div class="example">
            <p class="exampleHeadTextEmpty">example—do not break</p>
            <p MadCap:conditions="LingoGuides.LingoTranslationGuide,Products.LingoOnlineOnly">Let's say you import a Word document and the segments look like this in the Translation Editor:</p>
            <p MadCap:conditions="Products.Align,LingoGuides.LingoAlignmentGuide">Let's say you open an alignment project and the segments look like this in the Alignment Tool:</p>
            <p MadCap:conditions="Products.LingoOnlineOnly,LingoGuides.LingoTranslationGuide">
                <img src="../../Images/segmentation_rules2.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
            <p MadCap:conditions="Products.Align,LingoGuides.LingoAlignmentGuide">
                <img src="../../Images/segmentation_rules2_align.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
            <p MadCap:conditions="LingoGuides.LingoTranslationGuide,Products.LingoOnlineOnly">Notice that the first two rows should be joined into a single segment, and the final three rows should be joined together as well.</p>
            <p MadCap:conditions="Products.Align,LingoGuides.LingoAlignmentGuide">Notice that the segments are already aligned, but they are not segmented the way you want. The first two rows should be joined into a single segment, and the final three rows should be joined together as well.</p>
            <MadCap:pageBreak MadCap:conditions="LingoGuides.LingoAlignmentGuide,LingoGuides.LingoTranslationGuide" />
            <p>To accomplish this with segmentation rules, you can do the following:</p>
            <p>
                <img src="../../Images/segmentation_rules3.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
            <p MadCap:conditions="Products.LingoOnlineOnly,LingoGuides.LingoTranslationGuide">With these rules in place, you can update the project and the segments will look like this:</p>
            <p MadCap:conditions="Products.Align,LingoGuides.LingoAlignmentGuide">With these rules in place, you can reimport the project and the segments will look like this:</p>
            <p MadCap:conditions="LingoGuides.LingoTranslationGuide,Products.LingoOnlineOnly">
                <img src="../../Images/segmentation_rules4.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
            <p MadCap:conditions="Products.Align,LingoGuides.LingoAlignmentGuide">
                <img src="../../Images/segmentation_rules4_align.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
        </div>
        <MadCap:pageBreak MadCap:conditions="LingoGuides.LingoAlignmentGuide,LingoGuides.LingoTranslationGuide" />
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="ExampleBreak.flsnp" />
